        Product Description

        The Ninja Nutri-Blender Plus is the perfect tool for making healthy recipes in the kitchen. Pro Extractor Blades Assembly fully breaks down ingredients, unlocking the full potential of your fruits and veggies. It also perfectly crushes ice for smoothies, shakes, and frozen drinks. Blend directly in a 20 oz. Ninja To-Go Cup, then pop on a Spout Lid and take your favorite drinks on the go.

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        5 out of 5 stars
        Bestest Ninja blender for the price.. a s-blended experience
        So I FINALLY bought myself a new blender after my cheap nutribullet walmart one broke down on me a year ago (that thing put up with me for like 5 years though so it did its job for being like $20 lol). Heres my review This thing is like the Rolls-Royce of smaller blenders!! It was on sale too so I could justify spending like $70 on a new blender if it meant it would be heavier duty. I just tested it out today making myself a fruit/spinach/protein smoothie for lunch and its amazing!! The two cups that come with it are each about 24oz size (recommends max fill to be 21oz) so to be honest it makes a pretty large capacity for being a smaller blender. Its not a super clunky giant heavy machine so its easy to store and fits in my smaller sized cabinet just fine, which I extra love. The smoothie button will automatically do its thing and run its cycle but since I didnt put a ton of ice in mine, I cut it short by touching the button to turn it off after 40ish seconds. Turned out perfectly blended! I will be using the heck out of this thing for smoothies, hummus, and margarita recipes to say the least! My only comment is that I wish the cups that came with it were made out of glass.. not a huge fan of plastic things (especially for blenders) but such is the American way nowadays. Overall, yes get the Ninja!! Perfect size for single person household or for a couple.
